{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Should be consider removing `camera.aspect`? Or defaulting it to `null`? That way we deal with things like this automatically. But I don't know if this would mean having to compute the `projectionMatrix` every frame...\n\nAlternatively, we could indeed have a `renderer.getSize()` so people can deal with this issue.\n","created_at":"2015-01-20T15:13:49.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917#issuecomment-70668659","id":70668659,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcwNjY4NjU5","updated_at":"2015-01-20T15:13:49.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/70668659","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Running into this very issue, in an unusual project that has 8 displays horizontally (8x1920x1080), a list of observations:\n- Past 5760 pixels the canvas begins to get \"stretched\", eg one pixel will start taking up two or more pixels\n- As mentioned, aspect ratio becomes incorrect\n- renderer.setViewport \/ setScissor no longer causes renderer to paint at the right areas\n- Canvas is still the correct size, all things considered\n\n@greggman what are the current workarounds, even if I have to make a hacked build of THREE to make this work?\n","created_at":"2015-02-03T23:53:38.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917#issuecomment-72762554","id":72762554,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcyNzYyNTU0","updated_at":"2015-02-03T23:55:10.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/72762554","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1041360?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mflux","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDEzNjA=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mflux","type":"User","id":1041360,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I don't think you have to hack anything for most apps. In your own code do something like \n\n```\n    camera.aspect = renderer.domElement.clientWidth \/ renderer.domElement.clientHeight;\n```\n\nFor viewport assuming you want the entire canvas do this\n\n```\n    renderer.setViewport(\n         0, 0, renderer.context.drawingBufferWidth, renderer.context.drawingBufferHeight);\n```\n\nFor scissor your kind of on your own. You could try normalizing like\n\n```\n    renderer.setScissor(\n         x * renderer.context.drawingBufferWidth \/ renderer.domElement.clientWidth, \n         y * renderer.context.drawingBufferHeight \/ renderer.domElement.clientHeight,\n         width * renderer.context.drawingBufferWidth \/ renderer.domElement.clientWidth,\n         height * renderer.context.drawingBufferHeight \/ renderer.domElement.clientHeight);\n```\n\nIf you need the same dimensions for the viewport do the same normalization.\n\nGive it a try, tell me if it works.  \n","created_at":"2015-02-04T00:07:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917#issuecomment-72764317","id":72764317,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcyNzY0MzE3","updated_at":"2015-02-04T00:07:17.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/72764317","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/234804?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/greggman","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzNDgwNA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"greggman","type":"User","id":234804,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/greggman\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Well, this is \"fixed\" by using Firefox ;) Thankfully the project I'm working on does not require a specific browser, and FF performs just fine.\n\nMuch appreciated on the solution though! I will keep this in mind, up until Chrome \/ Safari decide to fix their canvases.\n","created_at":"2015-02-04T00:07:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917#issuecomment-72764318","id":72764318,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5917","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcyNzY0MzE4","updated_at":"2015-02-04T00:08:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/72764318","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1041360?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mflux","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDEzNjA=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mflux\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mflux","type"